{ If we are in time to solidify our centre we have a pleasant edge, so it's up to Black to create quick counterplay.   Note that  12...Bb7  loses a piece to  13.d5! }
12... Re8 13. Ng5
{ A complicated way of trying to gain some time. Both the e8-rook and our knight will have to retreat, but we are forcing a concession before that happens. }
13... Rf8 14. Re1 Bb7 { This is the move our move order is intended to stop! }
15. Nxf7 Rxf7 16. Bxf7+ Kxf7 17. d5
{ This is the point. Due to the double attack on c6 and a7 we win a piece, leaving us an exchange up. }
17... Bxe3 18. dxc6
{ Without the bishop on b7 Black would be in time to retreat the e3-bishop. } *

