{ Important. After having given up the bishop on f6, we always trade on b5 so that Black can't block with ...b4. }
14... axb5 15. Bd5
{ A key move, trading off the light-squared bishops. If Black takes on d5, then the a5-knight becomes a bit stuck. Next, up, we intend to double on the a-file, and in the long-term trade all but the f6-bishop. }
*

