14... exd4 15. cxd4 Bg4
{ The critical way. Black puts pressure on our centre. } 16. d5
{ Forced, but the resulting structure gives us a nice space advantage. } 16...
Nc4 17. h3 { Forcing the bishop to choose. } 17... Bxf3 18. gxf3
{ Necessary, as  18.Qxf3  Nxd5  would drop a pawn.  After 18.gxf3 a strategically very interesting position has occurred. We have the two bishops and a serious space advantage, but a somewhat weakened king. The knight on g3 is an excellent defender though, and the open g-file can be used for an attack. Our main plan consists of pushing either f4-f5 or f4-e5, perhaps combined with a march of the h-pawn. }
