11... O-O 12. Be3 exd4 13. cxd4 Nxe4
{ Does not, in fact, lose a piece, but is very dubious for Black. } 14. Qc2 Qe8
{ The only move to not lose a piece. } 15. Nc3
{ Gives White excellent compensation for the pawn. } 15... Nf6 16. Rfe1 Qd7
{ Was played in Tari-Praggnanandha, 2017. The problem for Black is that they lost too much time capturing the e4-pawn instead of developing their pieces, so the White attack now quickly becomes too strong. }
17. Ne4 { Is a good way to activate our pieces and remove a defender. } 17...
Nxe4 18. Qxe4
{ There are too many threats and especially too few defenders. White can make use of both the c- and e-files apart from all the light pieces. }
