11... O-O 12. Be3 Re8
{ Caruana's choice against Grischuk in the 2020 Candidates, therefore, the absolute mainline. Also Sethuraman's recommendation in his Lifetime Repertoire on the Arkhangelsk. By delaying ...Ra8 Black intends to gain some time and get an improved version of the 12...Ra8 lines. }
13. Ng5
{ This is a very advanced move. Normally the move Ng5 in similar positions is just an invitation for a repetition, but here we have a very concrete reason for doing it.  13.Re1  exd4  14.cxd4  was Grischuk-Caruana, but here Black's move order allows them to play  14...Nxe4!  which equalized in the game. }
13... Re7 { This does not work here as the rook will be hanging later on. } 14.
dxe5 Bxe3 15. exf6
{ The rook is hanging on e7, so Black does not have time to capture the g5-knight. }
