20... Bxd4 { is critical but does not work out so well. } 21. Red1 c5 22. Bxd4
cxd4 23. Nxf7
{ Black will get two pieces for the rook, but on the open board the rook is superior. Additionally, the Black king is weak.  23...Rxf7  24.Rxc8+  Bxc8  25.Qxe4  followed by Rxd4 is promising for us. The position is open, which benefits our rook. Additionally Black still has some issues with the weak king, while there is no obvious counterplay in sight. }
