16... Rfe8 17. Qd4 c5 18. dxc6 Nxc6 19. Qb6
{ with continuous pressure. The d6 and b5 pawns are slightly vulnerable, and the b3-bishop is more active than the one on b7. I suspect Black will manage to liquidate into something drawish with good play, but it's definitely a pleasant position for us. }
