6. c3 { As in the Arkhangelsk we occupy the centre. } 6... O-O
{ This is the start of the Neo-Møller. Black plays in a provocative manner, not really putting up any fight in the centre for the time being. On the other hand, Black has already managed to castle and has kept flexibility with the d-pawn. }
7. d4
{ Occupying the centre. If we manage to keep both central pawns intact we will have a very nice edge, but there will soon be heavy pressure against them. }
7... Ba7
{ This is Black's idea. As our e-pawn is hanging,  8.dxe5  Nxe4  would only be a trade which eases Black's defence. }
8. Re1
{ Defending the e-pawn. Again, all that we need is to stabilize the centre in order to claim a nice edge. }
8... d6 9. h3
