16. Ne3 Be6
{ The strongest move! It looks funny to retreat the bishop back to e6 again, but Black's logic is that Ne3 now is misplaced. }
17. b3
{ As the e3-knight blocks our c1-bishop we instead develop it on the other side. Next, we go Ba3, Qd2 and bring our rook into the game. Again the problem for Black is that ... d4 gives up the e4-square and ...e4 gives up the d4-squares, both things that will help us get stability. }
