{ It does not matter with which knight we are going to d4, as we are anyway intending to recapture with the other knight. }
13... Nxd4 14. Nxd4 c5 { Necessary, as Black needs to force White's hand. } 15.
Nxe6 Qxe6 16. f3 { Finally kicking the knight away from e4. } 16... Ng5
{ The only square, but a little bit clumsy. This position has been reached in thousands of games and is one of the absolute main positions of the Open Spanish. We have the bishop pair, but for the time being our bishops are pretty blocked and there is no obvious way of opening up for them. One of the main ideas is therefore to trade on g5, trying to prove that the light-squared bishop is stronger than Black's dark-squared one. This is true, but often White's advantage proves too small to really play for the win. }
