{ The only move, as Black needs to have time to pick up the a4-bishop next. }
10. Rxe5 bxa4
{ A very interesting and strategically imbalanced position has arisen. Black's structure on the queenside is dubious and the king is stuck in the centre, but they do have a bishop pair that can potentially be very strong. We should not get materialistic here and go for the a4-pawn, but rather act quickly in the centre before Black gets their king to safety. }
11. Qe2
{ An important move, creating an unpleasant pin on the e7-bishop and stopping O-O. }
11... Be6
{ This is the second most popular move, but in some sense the most logical one. Black tries to solve the problems on the e-file while developing at the same time. }
12. f4
