11. cxd4 O-O { A cunning move, not bothering to defend the e5-pawn. } 12. h3
{ 12.dxe5  dxe5  13.Nxe5  Qc7  shows why it's so important for Black to trade on d4 first - with the c-file open the bishop on c2 is hanging loose and Black gets a lot of counterplay on the c- and d-files. }
