{ A common tactical theme in these lines - the clack queen can't defend both the a8-rook and the knight on f6. }
16... Nxe4 17. Bxe4
{ The most active and direct move.  17.bxc6  Bxc6  18.Nxd4  is a solid alternative, giving us slightly the better structure and a small edge. }
17... axb5 18. Rxa8 Qxa8 19. Nxd4
{ We are threatening to take on b5, and if Black defends with  19...b4  we can simply increase the pressure with  20.Bf4  . Even with the limited material we are enjoying nice pressure. The c7-pawn is weak, and an interesting way to increase pressure further on could be to play Nf3, hitting the d7-bishop and potentially intending Ne5 later if the c6-knight moves. It's not a huge edge, but it looks quite unpleasant for Black to defend. }
