8. a4
{ Highlighting the drawback of delaying ...d6 - Black does not have ...Bd7 as a possible reply here.  8.c3  d5!  would be fine for Black. }
8... b4 9. a5 d5
{ is too ambitious - generally speaking Black only pushes ...d5 once White has committed the pawn to c3, as after exd5 Nxd5 the knight would then have something to attack. }
10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Re1 { Is simply a good version for us. } 11... Bb7 12. Nxe5
{ Not fearing any ghosts. This is not a Marshall, and Black is far from creating the usual amount of threats. }
12... Nxe5 13. Rxe5 Bf6 14. Re1
{ Our position is very solid, and Black can't really stop us from developing the rest of our pieces. }
14... Qd7 15. Nd2 Rae8 16. Ba4
{ is a last useful idea to keep in mind. We force further trades and Black gets less and less compensation for the pawn. }
