Bxa2 15. Rxe5 Be6 16. Rxa5
{ We have won a pawn, but Black has an interesting idea in mind. } 16... c5
{ The idea. Our rook on a5 is trapped, and in order to free it we have to give back our extra pawn. This has been played a few times and isn't all that bad for Black, but I still believe we have a little something. }
17. d4 { The simplest way, immediately freeing up our rook. } 17... cxd4 18.
Bf4
{ The bishop can later go to e5, putting pressure on the d4-pawn and the knight on f6. We have slightly the better structure and will be able to bring the last pieces into the game with Qd3 on the next move. It isn't a huge edge, but Black constantly has to worry about the d4, b4, and a6-pawns without having too much in return. }
