{ Looks ridiculous, but in fact very smart. We have lost one move, Black can't defend against the threat of d4 in a good way. }
13... Na5
{ The best try. Black is playing in the style of the Marshall attack, giving up a pawn for the bishop pair. }
14. Rxe5 Rxe5 15. Nxe5 Nxb3 16. axb3
{ We have won a pawn. Black does certainly have some compensation, especially the light-squared bishop will be quite useful on b7, but our position is solid and we will be in time to develop our remaining pieces and keep the extra pawn. }
