{ This is how Svidler himself played against Nepomniachtchi in 2020. } 16. d5
{ is a good response, as the knight lacks good squares. } 16... Nb4 17. Bb1
{ Threatening to trap the knight. } 17... a5 18. a3 Na6 19. b4
{ A typical idea in these positions, dominating the a6-knight. } 19... Bd7 20.
Bd2
{ gave a pleasant edge to Nepomniachtchi in the game. Next, we can follow up with Bd3, Qe2 and fight frot the a- and c-files. }
