{ Again h3 is the more popular move, but again I don't see any clear need for it yet. }
14... exd4 { 14...cxd4  15.cxd4  exd4  16.Nxd4  transposes to the same. } 15.
cxd4 cxd4 16. Nxd4
{ The structure is slightly better for White. It is very difficult to get real pressure against the d6-pawn, but the space advantage is very useful. Next, we can calmly develop with b3, Bb2 and then bring the a1-rook into the game. As Black finds it difficult to break out with ...d5 we have a small but very stable edge. }
