{ Again the e3-square turns out to be quite good for the queen. Next, we can move the f3-knight to either d2 or h2, followed by Qf3 pushing Black back. }
15... Be6
{ Prophylaxis against N3d2 or a later Ne3, but not an inspiring move to make. It is difficult to suggest anything better though. }
16. Rd1 Bd6 17. N3h2
{ We have a very pleasant position. Black's strategy with ... Nh5 has not really paid any dividends, and we are ready to take over the initiative. After Qf3 we have many ways to strengthen the position, for instance Ne3-f5 or Ne3-d5. Another long-term idea will be to push the pawns on the kingside, either h4-h5 or g4. The main problem for Black is again the lack of relevant counterplay. }
