{ Generally speaking it would also make sense to keep the knights, but we have a concrete idea in mind. }
13... Nxd4 14. cxd4 f5 { The only logical follow-up. } 15. Nf3
{ Threatening to win the queen! } 15... Nh4
{ Saving the queen by tactical means. } 16. exf5 b5
{ The best try, but not enough. } 17. Nxh4
{ There are other ways, but this is simple and effective. } 17... Qxh4 18. Bc2
Bxf5 19. Bxf5 Rxf5 20. a4
{ Black has managed to restore material equality and we are not winning anything immediately, but the c-file and Black's queenside pawns are very vulnerable. It might look threatening with the queen on h4 and rook on f5, but we have our own weakness on f2 very safely protected, and Black's bishop will never be able to join the attack. }
