12. Na3 { Continuing with our plan. } 12... f5 13. Nc4 f4
{ The most reasonable way. Black is trying to go all-out on the kingside. } 14.
b4
{ The fastest way of creating play. We are not afraid of giving up a pawn if it means we will get a big initative in the centre. With an open centre the knight on h5 and pawn on f4 would look very clumsy. }
14... exd4 15. cxd4 Nxb4 16. Ba3 Nxc2 17. Qxc2
{ This is the sort of position we are aiming for. We are a pawn down, but all our pieces are very well placed whereas Black completely lacks coordination. Our idea is to push the central pawns further, for instance by moving the a1-rook and then pushing d5. Also putting pressure on the b- and c-pawns makes sense. It is a very long-term initiative for the pawn, based on Black's lack of both coordination and counterplay. }
