{ 3...a6  4.Ba4  g6  5.c3  Nge7  or @@StartFEN@@r1bqkbnr/1ppp1ppp/p1n5/4p3/B3P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R b KQkq - 1 4@@EndFEN@@  4...Nge7  5.c3  g6  , are alternative move orders simply transposing into the same line. }
4. c3 a6 5. Ba4 Nge7 6. d4 exd4 7. cxd4 b5 8. Bc2 d5
{ This has been played a fair bit and is a typical reaction to our Bc2, as the bishop does not attack d5. However, I don't think it's the best moment for Black to play ...d5 though. }
