{ countertrickiness! } 21. bxc3 Rae8 { The most solid defense. } 22. cxd4 Qxd4
23. Rc6
{ We have a slight but persistent edge, as our bishop attacks f7 whereas our f2-pawn is safe. I suspect Black is making a draw with good play, but it does look pretty unpleasant. For instance  23...Rxe5  24.Rd1  Qe4  25.Qxe4  Rxe4  26.Rxa6  , followed by Ra7 and potentially doubling on the 7th rank. Both b5 and f7 are targets, and although the limited material gives Black decent drawing chances it's definitely not a draw just yet. If you find this to be too little, then castling long on move 15 is a more ambitious choice. }
