5... exd4 6. cxd4 a6
{ Black can't really do without this move in the long run. } 7. Ba4 b5 8. Bc2
{ Always our preferred square when given the option. The bishop protects e4, but most importantly it does not give Black a tempo with ...Na5 later on. With the knight still on c6 Black can't push c5, which often is the key plan. }
