4. c3 Bg7
{ This has been the most popular route to the mainline recently, but all of the move orders are likely to transpose. }
5. d4
{ Again it is important that we delay O-O, as we often have more pressing matters to do in the centre. }
5... exd4 6. cxd4 a6
{ Black can't really do without this move in the long run. } 7. Ba4 b5 8. Bc2
{ Always our preferred square when given the option. The bishop protects e4, but most importantly it does not give Black a tempo with ...Na5 later on. With the knight still on c6 Black can't push c5, which often is the key plan. }
8... d6
{ The most popular move. Black develops naturally, at the same time preventing us from pushing our d-pawn too far. }
9. d5 Na5 { The most common, and best move. } 10. O-O Ne7 11. Nc3
{ Just developing peacefully.  11.Bd2  Bxb2  12.Bxa5  Bxa1  13.Nc3  Bb2  is not as clear as without O-O d6 included, as we don't have the d6-break ourselves. Still, it gives very interesting compensation and is certainly a tempting option if you prefer much sharper play. }
11... O-O 12. Re1
{ The most flexible move, keeping the option of h4 in one go! Now our next couple of moves depend a lot on what Black is doing. As soon as they go ...Bb7 we play h4, as ...Bg4 is then no longer an option. If not, then h3 and developing the dark-squared bishop makes sense. The prophylactic move Rb1 can also frequently be an interesting move, both protecting b2 and stepping out of the long diagonal. }
12... Re8
{ The most flexible move, and therefore also the best.   12...Bb7  13.h4!  is just a very bad version of the main line for Black. }
13. h3 { Stopping ...Bg4, and waiting for Black to make their next move. }
13... Bb7 { By far the most natural move, and played in all games so far. } 14.
h4
{ Very weird looking, but the point is that h4-h5-h6 is such a strong plan that it makes sense also a tempo down!  14.Nh2  is also interesting and tempting, but I think 14.h4 is a bit more straightforward to play. }
14... h5 15. Bg5
{ Shows the strength of h4. The bishop is powerful on g5, and Black can't really kick it out with ...f6 as it would terminally weaken the e6-square. }
