14... c6
{ The only move that makes sense, as Black really needs counterplay in the centre. }
15. dxc6 Bxc6 { Looks natural, but after } 16. h5
{ we are developing a pretty serious initiative for free. } 16... Nc4 17. h6
Bh8
{ The point is that the pawn on h6, in the best AlphaZero style, is a big asset for a very long time. Black will always have back rank issues, and a lot of the endings will be bad as the h6-pawn is so close to promoting if h7 falls. Meanwhile, at the rest of the board we have a solid position, and can just continue normally. }
18. Bb3
{ Intending Bxc4 followed by Bg5, just increasing the pressure. Black has very little to compensate for our superpawn on h6. }
