{ The only move that makes sense, as Black really needs counterplay in the centre. }
15. dxc6 Nexc6 16. Bg5
{ Developing with tempo.  16.h5  Nb4!  intending a quick ...d5 would give Black quite a bit more counterplay than on the last move. }
16... Qc8
{ The only move that makes sense, as Nd5 would otherwise come with tempo. } 17.
Nd5
{ The position is almost completely winning for us and from a distance, it would require great nerves and skill from Black to allow this. }
17... Nd4 { Utilizing a tactical trick to trade off our monster knight. } 18.
Nxd4 { 18.Nf6+  Bxf6  19.Bxf6  Nxc2  unfortunately doesn't work for White. }
18... Bxd5 19. h5
{ Black has managed to trade our knight and keep the attack under control for the time being, but the pressure is far from over. With the text, we again intend to push h6, which would give us a significant positional advantage. Black will certainly have to display a great deal of accuracy in order to survive this, if at all possible. }
