1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nd4
{ Bird's Defence. Black moves an already developed piece again, which rarely is a good idea. }
4. Nxd4 exd4 5. O-O
{ As so often with the provocative sidelines, the strategy should be to meet them with solid, natural central play. }
5... Bc5 6. Bc4
{ A small subtlety. By threatening Bxf7+ we force Black to play d6, so that ...d5 never becomes a concern. }
