1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Bc5
{ This is a rare guest in top level practice, but still seen from time to time as a surprise weapon. Black is intending ... Nd4 to trade a set of knights. }
4. c3 Nf6 5. d4 exd4 6. e5 Ne4 7. O-O d5 8. cxd4
{ We have reached a very topical position in the Italian, but as our bishop went to b5 in one move, we have a clear extra tempo! Needless to say, that is enough for a nice advantage. }
8... Bb6 9. h3
{ Stops ...Bg4, intending Nc3, Be3 etc. We have a solid centre and a nice edge. }
