10. Bc2 { As usual we retreat all the way to c2 once given a chance. } 10...
Bb7 11. a4
{ We have seen this idea several times in the positions with the bishop on e7. We are trying to force the b-pawn to b4, giving us a square on c4. }
11... b4 12. a5 { Prevents Black from connecting the pawns with ...a5. } 12...
bxc3 { Has been the most popular choice, but looks like a concession. } 13.
bxc3 Na7
{ Black is trying to regroup creatively, but it does not make an impressive appearance. }
14. Na3 Nb5 15. Bd2
{ Looks like a simple enough solution. Next we can either push d4 or continue to maneuver with Nc4. It Is again very hard for Black to generate counterplay. }
