10. Be3 { Makes sense, as ...f5 is not coming anytime soon. } 10... Re8
{ 10...h6  11.Nbd2  Re8  12.b4  transposes. } 11. Nbd2 h6 12. b4
{ A logical move, grabbing space on the queenside. This was tried by the Chessable author Maaike Keetman! }
12... b5 13. Bb3 a5 14. a3
{ This was Keetman's game, and I believe she was doing quite well, though things went downhill later in the game  (Keetman, Maaike vs. Talsma, Paul A., lichess.org INT, 2020)  . Next up are moves like Qc2 and Rab1 or Reb1, forcing a decision from Black on the queenside. }
