10... b5
{ A natural move, as our a4-reaction will lose a tempo later on.   10...Re8  11.Be3  d5  12.Nbd2  b5  13.Bc2  a5  leads to the same line. }
11. Bc2 d5 12. Be3 dxe4 13. dxe4 Qxd1 14. Rxd1
{ Is not at all a drawish ending. We have a beautiful square on c5 for a knight, and the b5-pawn is vulnerable. Meanwhile, Black have very little to activity of their own. }
