15... g4 { An interesting idea that we will also see in the mainline. } 16.
hxg4 Bxg4 17. Bh4
{ is an annoying pin. The position looks quite scary for Black, and I am not sure the counterplay will come fast enough. }
17... bxc3 18. bxc3 Kg7
{ Protecting f6, thereby preparing the maneuver ...Ne7-g6 to get rid of the pin. }
19. d4
{ A logical moment for this, as Black is not yet coordinated. We are enjoying a nice initiative, and taking the pawn does not work out at all for Black: }
19... exd4 20. e5 Nxe5 21. Ne4 Ned7 22. cxd4
{ Gives us an overwhelming initiative for the pawn. The h4-d8 pin is an eternal issue for Black and we have plenty of time to increase pressure step by step. Moves like Qd3 followed by Ng3-f5 will likely be too much for Black to handle. }
