15... Ba7 { Continuing to wait... } 16. Re1
{ Overprotecting e4, and preparing Nf1-e3, but mainly continuing the waiting game.  16.Rc1  was also interesting, but  16...Na5  is an annoying reply. }
16... g4
{ Initiating more concrete play. If Black would do nothing, then either Rc1 or Nf1-e3 next would continue to improve our position. }
17. hxg4 Nxg4
{ Black's point is that Re1 has weakened the f2-pawn. On the other hand, ...g4 is a very commital decision, giving Black a worse structure and us a nice square on h4 for the knight or the bishop. However, the position is still quite sharp. }
18. Qe2
{ I like this move, overprotecting the f2-pawn and preparing Nh4. The immediate  18.Nh4  runs into  18...Nxf2!  19.Bxf2  Bxf2+  20.Kxf2  Qxh4  . }
18... Ne7 19. Nh4 { Would leave us in full control over the kingside. } *

