10. a4 { The typical response. } 10... Bd7
{ The most challenging move. Black is not committing the pawn to b4. } 11. Bg5
{ Setting up a positional threat. } 11... Rb8 12. d4
{ A good moment to expand in the centre. We are toying with the idea of d5, after which ...Ne7 would allow us to take on f6. }
