19... dxe5 20. fxe5 Nxe5 21. Bxf6+ Qxf6 22. Rxf6 Be6
{ Amazingly, Black manages to stay in the game. Due to the counterthreat of Rh8+ Kg1 d3+, we have to give back a rook. }
23. Ra6
{ Simply intending to eliminate the dangerous b6-bishop, after which the attack ends. }
23... d3 24. Rxb6 Rxb6 25. Rf4 dxc2 26. Qxc2
{ All the crazy complications has ended, and we are left with a queen for rook and bishop. Normally that's a major material advantage, but here Black is well coordinated and is a favorite to create a fortress. Still, White keeps some chances, but more importantly, the level of accuracy demanded from Black to get here is overwhelmingly high. If you think it was too chaotic, then 14.Bg3 is of course playable as well, and leads to less tactical but perhaps not less interesting fight. }
