{ is one of many ways for Black to play, but a rather concrete one. } 12. Bc2
d5 { As usual, the main move to consider once retreating all the way to c2. }
13. exd5 Qxd5 { The typical recapture. } 14. Ng3
{ This sort of position frequently occurs in the Italian, but there Black hasn't normally committed to ...b5. As Black is not really attacking anything on the queenside, the move ...b5 is more of a weakening than a strength. }
14... Be6 15. Bd2
{ is one of many interesting ways to play. We intend to play Qc1, after which a sacrifice on h6 is always in the air. It's certainly playable for Black, but I believe we still keep a little pressure. Another idea is to play a4, massaging the weakness on b5 and perhaps gaining the a-file. }
