12. Bc2 Nf4 13. Nf1 g5
{ This is Black's point. It looks a bit bizarre, but the f4-knight is really a very strong piece, and Black can continue attacking with Kh8, Rg8 next. It's very provocative, but the position is surprisingly tricky for us to handle. }
14. Ne3 { Intending to immediately utilize the weak f5-square. } 14... Kh8
{ Undoubtedly Black's best reply. ...Rg8 followed by g4 is now on the agenda, so we have to act fast! }
15. Nf5 { The most direct move. } 15... Rg8 16. Nh2
{ is very good for us, as we are in time to stop the counterplay. } *

