[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "30. Anti-Berlin 6...d6 7.Re1 7th Move Alternatives"]
[Black "7...Ng4 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. c3 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. Re1 Ng4
{ Always a critical response in such positions when playing Re1 before h3. Black attacks f2, but more importantly opens up for the f-pawn. }
8. Re2 f5
{ The logical follow-up to the previous move. Now the play gets quite sharp. }
9. exf5 Qf6 { Black is trying to stop d4 for the time being. } 10. Bxc6
{ Giving up the bishop in order to force d4 through.  10.h3  Nxf2  11.Rxf2  Bxf2+  12.Kxf2  is a bit similar to our line in the Open Spanish, but here it seems to be that Black's counterplay is a little bit more dangerous. }
10... bxc6 11. d4 exd4 12. cxd4 Bb6 13. h3 { Kicking the knight back. } 13...
Nh6
{ We have removed the intruders and there is no longer any question of us coming under an attack anymore. However, we had to give up the bishop pair to achieve it, meaning that Black is now doing fairly well strategically. Therefore we should act quickly. }
14. Qb3+ Kh8 15. Bg5
{ Forcing Black to move the queen away from the defense of the h6-knight. }
15... Qxf5 16. Bxh6 gxh6 17. Nbd2
{ Black's king is very hard to to get at on h8, but we still have some initiative. Rae1, enter on e7 and then the maneuver Ne4-g3 will put Black under pressure. With the bishop pair in return, it is certainly double-edged, but it seems our play is somewhat more dangerous. For instance }
17... Rg8 18. Re7
{ Entering with the rook, intending to double on the 7th rank if allowed.  18.Rae1  or even the slower  18.Nf1  intending Ng3 are perfectly playable alternatives if the mainline looks too sharp. }
18... Qf6 19. Rae1 Bxh3
{ Looks scary, but our attack is as strong as Black's. } 20. Rf7 { Ice cold! }
20... Rxg2+ 21. Kh1 Qg6 { The only reasonable square. } 22. Nh4 Qh5 23. Ree7
Bf5 { The only move to cover h7. } 24. Kxg2 Qxh4 25. Qg3 Rg8
{ Forcing us to abandon the 7th rank with one rook. } 26. Rg7 Qxg3+ 27. Rxg3
{ The forced play is over and we have emerged with an extra exchange. Black certainly has drawing chances, but we are definitely pushing for the win! }
*

