[White "30. Anti-Berlin 6...d6 7.Re1 7th Move Alternatives"]
[Black "7...Bb6 8.a4 a5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. c3 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. Re1 Bb6
{ This is one of the best moves for Black. Voluntarily retreating the bishop looks odd, but we have frequently seen the d4-push being very strong due to attacking the c5-bishop. }
8. a4
{ A very direct reaction to 7...Bb6, actually threatening to trap the bishop!  Normally,  8.Nbd2  is a good reaction against ...Bb6, but here it runs into  8...Ng4!  and Black has an improved version of the 7...Ng4 lines, as there we didn't want to commit our knight to d2 so early. The alternative move @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/ppp2ppp/1bnp1n2/1B2p3/4P3/2PP1N2/PP3PPP/RNBQR1K1 w - - 2 8@@EndFEN@@  8.h3  stopping any Ng4, gives Black time for  8...Ne7  and after  9.d4  d5!  we are back to the position we are trying to avoid by playing 7.Re1 instead of 7.h3. }
8... a5
{ This is interesting, but as so often the inclusion of a4 a5 favours us. I have said it before, but the two main reasons are: the bishop is more vulnerable on b6 after a Nbd2-c4 and our rook can enter the game via a3. }
9. h3 Ne7 { Black plays as if a4 a5 isn't included. } 10. d4 d5 11. exd5
{ Normally not the way we want to capture, but here it makes a lot of sense. }
11... e4 12. Ng5 { Will just pick up the e4-pawn for free. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "30. Anti-Berlin 6...d6 7.Re1 7th Move Alternatives"]
[Black "7...Bb6 8.a4 a5 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. c3 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. Re1 Bb6
{ This is one of the best moves for Black. Voluntarily retreating the bishop looks odd, but we have frequently seen the d4-push being very strong due to attacking the c5-bishop. }
8. a4
{ A very direct reaction to 7...Bb6, actually threatening to trap the bishop!  Normally,  8.Nbd2  is a good reaction against ...Bb6, but here it runs into  8...Ng4!  and Black has an improved version of the 7...Ng4 lines, as there we didn't want to commit our knight to d2 so early. The alternative move @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/ppp2ppp/1bnp1n2/1B2p3/4P3/2PP1N2/PP3PPP/RNBQR1K1 w - - 2 8@@EndFEN@@  8.h3  stopping any Ng4, gives Black time for  8...Ne7  and after  9.d4  d5!  we are back to the position we are trying to avoid by playing 7.Re1 instead of 7.h3. }
