{ Normally not the way we want to capture, but here it makes a lot of sense. }
11... exd4 12. Bg5 { Forcing Black to choose with what to recapture on d5. }
12... Nexd5 13. cxd4 h6 14. Bh4
{ Is a typical sort of position where the isolated pawn is pretty strong. We have a nice outpost for our knight on e5, and the h4-d8 pin is quite annoying for Black @@StartBracket@@the bishop is far away on b6@@EndBracket@@. Next, we can play Nc3, Bc4 and Qb3, while waiting for a good moment to jump Ne5. }
14... Qd6 15. Nbd2 { Shows one reason why a4 a5 is beneficial for us. } *

